{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"SNG"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Song of Sulaiman \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Song of Sulaiman \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Song of Sulaiman \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Sng \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["The Song of Sulaiman \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"SNG 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"SNG 1:1"},"The Song of songs, which is Sulaiman’s. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"SNG 1:2"},"Let him kiss me with the kisses of his mouth; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for your love is better than wine. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"SNG 1:3"},"Your oils have a pleasing fragrance. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your name is oil poured out, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["therefore the virgins love you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"SNG 1:4"},"Take me away with you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let’s hurry. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The king has brought me into his rooms. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Friends \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["We will be glad and rejoice in you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["We will praise your love more than wine! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They are right to love you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"SNG 1:5"},"I am dark, but lovely, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you daughters of Jerusalem, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like Kedar’s tents, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like Sulaiman’s curtains. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"SNG 1:6"},"Don’t stare at me because I am dark, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because the sun has scorched me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My mother’s sons were angry with me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They made me keeper of the vineyards. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I haven’t kept my own vineyard. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"SNG 1:7"},"Tell me, you whom my soul loves, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["where you graze your flock, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["where you rest them at noon; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for why should I be as one who is veiled \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["beside the flocks of your companions? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"SNG 1:8"},"If you don’t know, most beautiful amongst women, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["follow the tracks of the sheep. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Graze your young goats beside the shepherds’ tents. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"SNG 1:9"},"I have compared you, my love, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to a steed in Pharaoh’s chariots. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"SNG 1:10"},"Your cheeks are beautiful with earrings, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your neck with strings of jewels. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Friends \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"SNG 1:11"},"We will make you earrings of gold, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with studs of silver. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"SNG 1:12"},"While the king sat at his table, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["my perfume spread its fragrance. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"SNG 1:13"},"My beloved is to me a sachet of myrrh, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that lies between my breasts. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"SNG 1:14"},"My beloved is to me a cluster of henna blossoms \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the vineyards of En Gedi. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"SNG 1:15"},"Behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used\nas an interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," you are beautiful, my love. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Behold, you are beautiful. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your eyes are like doves. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"SNG 1:16"},"Behold, you are beautiful, my beloved, yes, pleasant; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and our couch is verdant. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"SNG 1:17"},"The beams of our house are cedars. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Our rafters are firs. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"SNG 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"SNG 2:1"},"I am a rose of Sharon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a lily of the valleys. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"SNG 2:2"},"As a lily amongst thorns, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so is my love amongst the daughters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"SNG 2:3"},"As the apple tree amongst the trees of the wood, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so is my beloved amongst the sons. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I sat down under his shadow with great delight, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his fruit was sweet to my taste. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"SNG 2:4"},"He brought me to the banquet hall. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His banner over me is love. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"SNG 2:5"},"Strengthen me with raisins, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["refresh me with apples; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I am faint with love. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"SNG 2:6"},"His left hand is under my head. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His right hand embraces me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"SNG 2:7"},"I adjure you, daughters of Jerusalem, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the roes, or by the hinds of the field, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you not stir up, nor awaken love, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until it so desires. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"SNG 2:8"},"The voice of my beloved! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Behold, he comes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["leaping on the mountains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["skipping on the hills. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"SNG 2:9"},"My beloved is like a roe or a young deer. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Behold, he stands behind our wall! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He looks in at the windows. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He glances through the lattice. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"SNG 2:10"},"My beloved spoke, and said to me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Rise up, my love, my beautiful one, and come away. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"SNG 2:11"},"For behold, the winter is past. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The rain is over and gone. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"SNG 2:12"},"The flowers appear on the earth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The time of the singing has come, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the voice of the turtledove is heard in our land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"SNG 2:13"},"The fig tree ripens her green figs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The vines are in blossom. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They give out their fragrance. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Arise, my love, my beautiful one, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and come away.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"SNG 2:14"},"My dove in the clefts of the rock, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the hiding places of the mountainside, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["let me see your face. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["let me hear your voice; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for your voice is sweet and your face is lovely. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"SNG 2:15"},"Catch for us the foxes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the little foxes that plunder the vineyards; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for our vineyards are in blossom. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"SNG 2:16"},"My beloved is mine, and I am his. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He browses amongst the lilies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"SNG 2:17"},"Until the day is cool, and the shadows flee away, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["turn, my beloved, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and be like a roe or a young deer on the mountains of Bether.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"SNG 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"SNG 3:1"},"By night on my bed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I sought him whom my soul loves. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I sought him, but I didn’t find him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"SNG 3:2"},"I will get up now, and go about the city; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the streets and in the squares I will seek him whom my soul loves.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I sought him, but I didn’t find him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"SNG 3:3"},"The watchmen who go about the city found me; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Have you seen him whom my soul loves?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"SNG 3:4"},"I had scarcely passed from them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I found him whom my soul loves. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I held him, and would not let him go, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until I had brought him into my mother’s house, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["into the room of her who conceived me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"SNG 3:5"},"I adjure you, daughters of Jerusalem, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the roes, or by the hinds of the field, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you not stir up nor awaken love, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until it so desires. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"SNG 3:6"},"Who is this who comes up from the wilderness like pillars of smoke,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["perfumed with myrrh and frankincense, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with all spices of the merchant? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"SNG 3:7"},"Behold, it is Sulaiman’s carriage! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Sixty mighty men are around it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["of the mighty men of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"SNG 3:8"},"They all handle the sword, and are expert in war. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Every man has his sword on his thigh, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of fear in the night. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"SNG 3:9"},"King Sulaiman made himself a carriage \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["of the wood of Lebanon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"SNG 3:10"},"He made its pillars of silver, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["its bottom of gold, its seat of purple, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the middle of it being paved with love, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the daughters of Jerusalem. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"SNG 3:11"},"Go out, you daughters of Zion, and see king Sulaiman, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the crown with which his mother has crowned him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the day of his weddings, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the day of the gladness of his heart. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"SNG 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"SNG 4:1"},"Behold, you are beautiful, my love. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Behold, you are beautiful. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your eyes are like doves behind your veil. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your hair is as a flock of goats, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that descend from Mount Gilead. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"SNG 4:2"},"Your teeth are like a newly shorn flock, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which have come up from the washing, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["where every one of them has twins. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["None is bereaved amongst them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"SNG 4:3"},"Your lips are like scarlet thread. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your mouth is lovely. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your temples are like a piece of a pomegranate behind your veil.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"SNG 4:4"},"Your neck is like Dawood’s tower built for an armoury, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on which a thousand shields hang, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all the shields of the mighty men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"SNG 4:5"},"Your two breasts are like two fawns \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that are twins of a roe, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which feed amongst the lilies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"SNG 4:6"},"Until the day is cool, and the shadows flee away, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will go to the mountain of myrrh, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to the hill of frankincense. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"SNG 4:7"},"You are all beautiful, my love. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["There is no spot in you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"SNG 4:8"},"Come with me from Lebanon, my bride, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with me from Lebanon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Look from the top of Amana, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the top of Senir and Hermon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the lions’ dens, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the mountains of the leopards. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"SNG 4:9"},"You have ravished my heart, my sister, my bride. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You have ravished my heart with one of your eyes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with one chain of your neck. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"SNG 4:10"},"How beautiful is your love, my sister, my bride! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How much better is your love than wine, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the fragrance of your perfumes than all kinds of spices! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"SNG 4:11"},"Your lips, my bride, drip like the honeycomb. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Honey and milk are under your tongue. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The smell of your garments is like the smell of Lebanon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"SNG 4:12"},"My sister, my bride, is a locked up garden; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a locked up spring, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a sealed fountain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"SNG 4:13"},"Your shoots are an orchard of pomegranates, with precious fruits,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["henna with spikenard plants, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"SNG 4:14"},"spikenard and saffron, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["calamus and cinnamon, with every kind of incense tree; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["myrrh and aloes, with all the best spices, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"SNG 4:15"},"a fountain of gardens, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a well of living waters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["flowing streams from Lebanon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"SNG 4:16"},"Awake, north wind, and come, you south! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Blow on my garden, that its spices may flow out. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let my beloved come into his garden, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and taste his precious fruits. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"SNG 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"SNG 5:1"},"I have come into my garden, my sister, my bride. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have gathered my myrrh with my spice; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have eaten my honeycomb with my honey; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have drunk my wine with my milk. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Friends \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Eat, friends! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Drink, yes, drink abundantly, beloved. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"SNG 5:2"},"I was asleep, but my heart was awake. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is the voice of my beloved who knocks: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Open to me, my sister, my love, my dove, my undefiled; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for my head is filled with dew, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my hair with the dampness of the night.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"SNG 5:3"},"I have taken off my robe. Indeed, must I put it on? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have washed my feet. Indeed, must I soil them? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"SNG 5:4"},"My beloved thrust his hand in through the latch opening. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["My heart pounded for him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"SNG 5:5"},"I rose up to open for my beloved. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["My hands dripped with myrrh, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["my fingers with liquid myrrh, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on the handles of the lock. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"SNG 5:6"},"I opened to my beloved; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but my beloved left, and had gone away. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My heart went out when he spoke. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I looked for him, but I didn’t find him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I called him, but he didn’t answer. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"SNG 5:7"},"The watchmen who go about the city found me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They beat me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They bruised me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The keepers of the walls took my cloak away from me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"SNG 5:8"},"I adjure you, daughters of Jerusalem, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["If you find my beloved, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you tell him that I am faint with love. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Friends \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"SNG 5:9"},"How is your beloved better than another beloved, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you fairest amongst women? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["How is your beloved better than another beloved, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["that you do so adjure us? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"SNG 5:10"},"My beloved is white and ruddy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The best amongst ten thousand. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"SNG 5:11"},"His head is like the purest gold. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His hair is bushy, black as a raven. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"SNG 5:12"},"His eyes are like doves beside the water brooks, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["washed with milk, mounted like jewels. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"SNG 5:13"},"His cheeks are like a bed of spices with towers of perfumes.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His lips are like lilies, dropping liquid myrrh. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"SNG 5:14"},"His hands are like rings of gold set with beryl. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His body is like ivory work overlaid with sapphires. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"SNG 5:15"},"His legs are like pillars of marble set on sockets of fine gold.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His appearance is like Lebanon, excellent as the cedars. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"SNG 5:16"},"His mouth is sweetness; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yes, he is altogether lovely. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["This is my beloved, and this is my friend, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["daughters of Jerusalem. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"SNG 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Friends \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"SNG 6:1"},"Where has your beloved gone, you fairest amongst women? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Where has your beloved turned, that we may seek him with you?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"SNG 6:2"},"My beloved has gone down to his garden, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to the beds of spices, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to pasture his flock in the gardens, and to gather lilies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"SNG 6:3"},"I am my beloved’s, and my beloved is mine. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He browses amongst the lilies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"SNG 6:4"},"You are beautiful, my love, as Tirzah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["lovely as Jerusalem, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["awesome as an army with banners. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"SNG 6:5"},"Turn away your eyes from me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they have overcome me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your hair is like a flock of goats, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that lie along the side of Gilead. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"SNG 6:6"},"Your teeth are like a flock of ewes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which have come up from the washing, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["of which every one has twins; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["not one is bereaved amongst them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"SNG 6:7"},"Your temples are like a piece of a pomegranate behind your veil.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"SNG 6:8"},"There are sixty queens, eighty concubines, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and virgins without number. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"SNG 6:9"},"My dove, my perfect one, is unique. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She is her mother’s only daughter. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She is the favourite one of her who bore her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The daughters saw her, and called her blessed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The queens and the concubines saw her, and they praised her.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"SNG 6:10"},"Who is she who looks out as the morning, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["beautiful as the moon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["clear as the sun, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and awesome as an army with banners? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"SNG 6:11"},"I went down into the nut tree grove, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to see the green plants of the valley, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to see whether the vine budded, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the pomegranates were in flower. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"SNG 6:12"},"Without realising it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["my desire set me with my royal people’s chariots. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Friends \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"SNG 6:13"},"Return, return, Shulammite! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Return, return, that we may gaze at you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why do you desire to gaze at the Shulammite, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as at the dance of Mahanaim? \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"SNG 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"SNG 7:1"},"How beautiful are your feet in sandals, prince’s daughter! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your rounded thighs are like jewels, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the work of the hands of a skilful workman. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"SNG 7:2"},"Your body is like a round goblet, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no mixed wine is wanting. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your waist is like a heap of wheat, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["set about with lilies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"SNG 7:3"},"Your two breasts are like two fawns, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that are twins of a roe. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"SNG 7:4"},"Your neck is like an ivory tower. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your eyes are like the pools in Heshbon by the gate of Bathrabbim.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your nose is like the tower of Lebanon which looks towards Damascus.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"SNG 7:5"},"Your head on you is like Carmel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The hair of your head like purple. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The king is held captive in its tresses. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"SNG 7:6"},"How beautiful and how pleasant you are, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["love, for delights! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"SNG 7:7"},"This, your stature, is like a palm tree, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your breasts like its fruit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"SNG 7:8"},"I said, “I will climb up into the palm tree. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will take hold of its fruit.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let your breasts be like clusters of the vine, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the smell of your breath like apples. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"SNG 7:9"},"Your mouth is like the best wine, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that goes down smoothly for my beloved, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["gliding through the lips of those who are asleep. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"SNG 7:10"},"I am my beloved’s. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His desire is towards me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"SNG 7:11"},"Come, my beloved! Let’s go out into the field. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let’s lodge in the villages. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"SNG 7:12"},"Let’s go early up to the vineyards. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let’s see whether the vine has budded, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["its blossom is open, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the pomegranates are in flower. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["There I will give you my love. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"SNG 7:13"},"The mandrakes produce fragrance. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["At our doors are all kinds of precious fruits, new and old, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which I have stored up for you, my beloved. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"SNG 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"SNG 8:1"},"Oh that you were like my brother, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who nursed from the breasts of my mother! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["If I found you outside, I would kiss you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yes, and no one would despise me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"SNG 8:2"},"I would lead you, bringing you into the house of my mother,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who would instruct me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I would have you drink spiced wine, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["of the juice of my pomegranate. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"SNG 8:3"},"His left hand would be under my head. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His right hand would embrace me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"SNG 8:4"},"I adjure you, daughters of Jerusalem, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you not stir up, nor awaken love, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until it so desires. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Friends \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"SNG 8:5"},"Who is this who comes up from the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["leaning on her beloved? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Under the apple tree I aroused you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["There your mother conceived you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["There she was in labour and bore you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"SNG 8:6"},"Set me as a seal on your heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as a seal on your arm; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for love is strong as death. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Jealousy is as cruel as Sheol.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Sheol is the place of the dead.\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Its flashes are flashes of fire, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a very flame of the LORD.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, “LORD” or “ALLAH” is the translation of\nAllah’s Proper Name."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"SNG 8:7"},"Many waters can’t quench love, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither can floods drown it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["If a man would give all the wealth of his house for love, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he would be utterly scorned. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Brothers \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"SNG 8:8"},"We have a little sister. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She has no breasts. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["What shall we do for our sister \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the day when she is to be spoken for? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"SNG 8:9"},"If she is a wall, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["we will build on her a turret of silver. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["If she is a door, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["we will enclose her with boards of cedar. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"SNG 8:10"},"I am a wall, and my breasts like towers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then I was in his eyes like one who found peace. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"SNG 8:11"},"Sulaiman had a vineyard at Baal Hamon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He leased out the vineyard to keepers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Each was to bring a thousand shekels",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 1000 shekels is\nabout 10 kilograms or about 22 pounds."]}],"caller":"+"}," of silver for its fruit.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"SNG 8:12"},"My own vineyard is before me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The thousand are for you, Sulaiman, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["two hundred for those who tend its fruit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Lover \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"SNG 8:13"},"You who dwell in the gardens, with friends in attendance, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["let me hear your voice! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"sp","content":["Beloved \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"SNG 8:14"},"Come away, my beloved! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Be like a gazelle or a young stag on the mountains of spices!\n"]}]}